5000|$|Currently, the {{fluoroquinolone}} antibiotics are {{the drugs}} of choice. Trimethoprim-sulfamethoxazole and doxycycline {{are no longer}} recommended because of high levels of resistance to these agents. [...] Antibiotics are typically given for three to five days, but single doses of azithromycin or levofloxacin have been used. [...] <b>Rifaximin</b> is approved in the U.S. for treatment of TD caused by ETEC. [...] If diarrhea persists despite therapy, travelers should be evaluated for bacterial strains resistant to the prescribed antibiotic, possible viral or parasitic infections, bacterial or amoebic dysentery, Giardia, helminths, or cholera.|$|E
